AUTONOMOUS MAINTENANCE SYSTEM

7.0 SENTRY-1 ROVER INTEGRATION

7.1 Health Assessment Algorithm

7.1.1 Weighted Health Score
H = \sum_{i=1}^{4} w_i \cdot S_i


Where weights:

· $w_1$ = 0.35 (Pressure integrity)
· $w_2$ = 0.40 (Spectral quality)
· $w_3$ = 0.15 (Physical integrity)
· $w_4$ = 0.10 (Thermal stability)

Scoring functions:

1. Pressure: $S_1 = \min\left(1, \frac{P}{0.8\ \text{kPa}}\right)$
2. Spectral: $S_2 = 1 - \min\left(1, 5 \cdot \gamma_{\text{crossover}}\right)$
3. Physical: $S_3 = \max\left(0, 1 - 0.2 \cdot N_{\text{punctures}}\right)$
4. Thermal: $S_4 = \exp\left[-\left(\frac{T - 20}{50}\right)^2\right]$

Decision matrix:

· $H \geq 0.8$: Monitor only
· $0.4 \leq H < 0.8$: In-situ repair
· $H < 0.4$: Full node replacement

7.2 Partially Observable Markov Decision Process

7.2.1 State Space:
$s = \langle H, D, T, F, R \rangle$
Where:

· $H$: Health score (continuous)
· $D$: Dust storm intensity (0-1)
· $T$: Time since last calibration (days)
· $F$: Environmental flux level
· $R$: Radiation alert status

7.2.2 Observation Model (with noise):
o = s + \mathcal{N}(0, \Sigma) + \delta_{\text{dust}} \cdot \mathcal{U}(-0.3, 0.3)


Where $\Sigma$ = diagonal covariance matrix, $\delta_{\text{dust}}$ = 1 if $D > 0.5$

7.2.3 Reward Function:
R(s,a) = 
\begin{cases}
+100 & \text{Node operational after repair} \\
-10 & \text{Unnecessary repair} \\
-50 & \text{Failed repair attempt} \\
-1000 & \text{Crew safety compromised}
\end{cases}

7.2.4 Optimal Policy via Value Iteration:
V^*(s) = \max_a \left[ R(s,a) + \gamma \sum_{s'} P(s'|s,a) V^*(s') \right]


Where $\gamma$ = 0.95 discount factor

7.3 Post-Swap Validation Protocol

7.3.1 PSV Packet Format (320 bytes)

```
Segment 1: Header (16B)
  - Timestamp: 8B (TAI ns)
  - Rover ID: 2B
  - Node ID: 2B
  - Transaction: 2B (0xAF01 = swap complete)
  - Reserved: 2B

Segment 2: Mechanical (32B)
  - Torque[3]: 3×2B (0.01 Nm resolution)
  - Alignment: 2B (0.01° resolution)
  - Connector impedance: 2B (mΩ)
  - Seal pressure: 2B (Pa)
  - Reserved: 20B

Segment 3: Detector Baseline (128B)
  - Dark noise: 4B (Hz)
  - He-3 pressure: 4B (0.001 atm)
  - PMT gains: 3×4B
  - Pedestals: 256×1B (per ADC channel)
  - Reserved: 12B

Segment 4: Calibration Proof (144B)
  - Cf-252 counts: 4B
  - Peak channel: 2B
  - FOM: 4B
  - Thermal CR: 4B (0.001 cps)
  - Spectrum: 64×2B
  - Checksum: 2B (CRC-16)
```

7.3.2 Validation Criteria
Node accepted if ALL conditions met:

1. $\left|\frac{\text{Peak}_{\text{meas}} - 2048}{2048}\right| < 0.01$
2. $\text{FOM} > 1.2$
3. $\left|\frac{\text{Thermal CR} - \text{Thermal}_{\text{model}}}{\text{Thermal}_{\text{model}}}\right| < 0.15$
4. All torques $= 12.0 \pm 0.5\ \text{Nm}$

8.0 RADIATION STORM RESPONSE

8.1 Predictive Algorithm

8.1.1 SPE Detection Confidence
C_{\text{SPE}} = \frac{N_{\text{agree}}}{N_{\text{total}}} \cdot \exp\left(-\frac{\Delta t}{\tau}\right)


Where:

· $N_{\text{agree}}$ = Number of nodes showing increase
· $\Delta t$ = Time since orbital warning
· $\tau$ = 30 minutes (plasma propagation uncertainty)

8.1.2 Dose Projection
H_{\text{proj}}(t + \Delta t) = H(t) + \int_t^{t+\Delta t} \dot{H}(\tau) \cdot f_{\text{shield}}(\tau) \ d\tau


Where $f_{\text{shield}}$ = 0.2-1.0 depending on Water Wall status

8.1.3 Optimization Problem
Minimize total crew dose:
\min_{t_{\text{act}}} \int_{t_0}^{t_{\text{end}}} H(t) \ dt


Subject to:

1. $t_{\text{act}} \geq t_{\text{now}} + 60\ \text{s}$ (activation delay)
2. Water consumption $\leq 1000\ \text{L}$ (storage limit)
3. Power draw $\leq 5\ \text{kW}$ (system limit)

8.2 Crew Safety Protocols

8.2.1 Personal Dose Limits

· 30 days: 250 mSv (ICRP Mars adaptation)
· Annual: 500 mSv
· Career: 1000 mSv (age-dependent)

8.2.2 ALARA Implementation
As Low As Reasonably Achievable optimization:
\text{Cost} = \sum_{i=1}^{N_{\text{crew}}} H_i + \lambda \cdot E_{\text{shield}} + \mu \cdot W_{\text{water}}


Where $\lambda = 0.01\ \text{Sv/J}$, $\mu = 0.001\ \text{Sv/L}$

