9.2 Dose Rate Accuracy

· Systematic uncertainty: < 15% (95% CI)
· Statistical uncertainty: < 5% at 1 µSv/h (1 hour average)
· Energy dependence: ±10% from 0.025 eV to 100 MeV
· Angular response: ±15% over 2π steradians

9.3 Detection Limits

· Minimum detectable flux: 0.1 n/cm²/s (thermal), 0.01 n/cm²/s (fast)
· Minimum dose rate: 0.05 µSv/h (8 hour integration)
· Hydrogen detection: 0.5% WEH in top 50 cm (24 hour survey)

