System reliability (3-node network, 1 spare):
R_{\text{system}}(t) = 1 - \left[1 - R_{\text{node}}(t)\right]^4


Where $R_{\text{node}}(t) = \exp(-t/\text{MTBF}_{\text{node}})$

10-year reliability: > 0.999

10.2 Radiation Hardness

· Total Ionizing Dose: 100 krad(Si) with < 10% performance degradation
· Single Event Effects: < 1 SEU/day at solar minimum, protected by triple modular redundancy
· Displacement damage: < 10¹¹ n/cm² (1 MeV equivalent) over 10 years

10.3 Environmental Tolerance

· Temperature cycles: 10,000 cycles (-100°C to +50°C)
